uggests any perovskite content\nat all. The fact that X-ray, dielectric, and hysteresis data all lead to the\nwrong conclusion is instructive and reminds us of earlier work on copper\ncalcium titanate (a well-known boundary-layer capacitor).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Jun 2019 16:43:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 28 Aug 2019 10:41:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-29"}
